{
    "attributes": {
        "action": "Make it illegal for doorbell footage to be used by companies for AI training",
        "additional_details": "People can be filmed by doorbell cameras as they walk down their own streets, then that footage can be used to by the company who made the doorbell camera to build AI tools which those filmed may never have consented to. We think that this is unfair and undermines trust in both technology and neighbours. In our view home security should protect homes, not turn the public into unpaid test data, and we do not think the law has kept up.\r\n\r\nParliament should set clear limits so people\u2019s faces, movements and daily routines cannot be used for AI training without real permission and proper safeguards.",
        "background": "Make it illegal for companies to use doorbell or home CCTV footage to train AI on recognisable people without permission. Only footage that is fully anonymised, with strict limits on use and storage, regular checks, and fines for breaking the rules should be allowed for this use.",
